Today it feels as though I am less anxious and less likely to get panicked. I know this is because my amygdala and other parts of my brain have naturally been conditioned to feel more anxious than usual.

I think the best way to describe myself right now is a hypochondriac since I was reasonably concerned about my health to where I was getting anxious about making / eating certain foods. Because I had previous experiences where I physically felt unwell after eating.
I've had help from not only the Crisis Text Line but also from a few other folks and some discord groups I'm in. They've been doing a good job at helping me understand what exactly is going on.

After going to the hospital everything seemed to have checked out fine except for my potassium levels. They gave me four pills for that though. They've essentially concluded that it was anxiety / panic. The few days after that I've been slowly managing my anxiety a lot easier.

About four or five days ago, I was working. To make it short, I had a panic attack that cost me to hyperventilate and feel really dizzy, tingly, and even have my hands freeze up. It was very scary and I wanted to go to the hospital.

So it's been awhile since I've written anything on here and I should explain why. For the past few weeks, I've been dealing with health issues initially. I think I've gotten better on that front. But now, I've recently been dealing with more feelings of anxiety and some panic.

At around 10pm tonight, I'm gonna try streaming some art. I'm trying to get back into the rhythm. HOWEVER, be aware that there'll be some downtime since I have to eat after work.

If you're in the fatchat Discord, I'll be in the voice channel.
